Business Brief -- American Steel  Wire Corp.:
   Firm Had 2nd-Quarter Loss,
   Expects Loss for Full Year
In fiscal 1991, the Cuyahoga Heights, Ohio, company posted
a loss of $4.05 million, or 48 cents a share.
   Separately, American Steel  Wire said it began
discussions with its lenders to revise loan agreements.
Although the company is no longer in compliance with some of
its lending terms, none of its lenders have declared
defaults.
   American Steel  Wire said it retained PaineWebber Inc. to
assist it in modifying the loan covenants and to help
"identify one or more strategic partners with the aggregate
capital and raw material resources necessary to enable us to
achieve our growth and continuous quality improvement
objectives in the 1990s."